==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mittimus
<hw>Mit"ti*mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., we send,
fr. <ets>mittere</ets> to send.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd>
<def>A precept or warrant granted by a justice for committing to prison
a party charged with crime; a warrant of commitment to prison.</def>
<au>Burrill.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A writ for removing records from one
court to another.</def> <au>Brande & C.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mittler's green</ent>⟦br⟧
